Just pick something out of thin air because I'm not using it directly.

00:07:06.760 --> 00:07:08.460
I'm not tracking its releases.

00:07:08.700 --> 00:07:14.120
I happen to maybe be using something that uses care debt that then, you know, if something happened to that package, I'm not saying it has.

00:07:14.180 --> 00:07:14.300
Right.

00:07:14.320 --> 00:07:18.320
Just like thinking of like really popular third party, third level dependencies.

00:07:18.320 --> 00:07:18.880
Yeah.

