Anyway, for context, this seems so long ago.

00:07:58.080 --> 00:07:59.040
June of 2025.

00:07:59.340 --> 00:08:00.460
It was less than a year ago.

00:08:01.320 --> 00:08:15.000
Simon Wilson wrote a blog post about the trifecta of AI agents of lethal, the lethal trifecta, which is giving them access to private data, exposure to untrusted content, and ability to externally communicate.

00:08:15.320 --> 00:08:21.480
That's pretty much what coding agents are like now, especially if you run it in YOLO mode or dangerous mode.

00:08:21.680 --> 00:08:21.960
Because...

00:08:22.580 --> 00:08:25.380
And it seems like people wouldn't do that, right?

00:08:25.440 --> 00:08:27.000
But it's so much faster.

00:08:27.460 --> 00:08:29.780
So if you don't...

00:08:29.780 --> 00:08:34.060
If you have your agents on like ask mode, it's just like, hey, can I run this command?

00:08:34.180 --> 00:08:34.440
Yes.

00:08:34.660 --> 00:08:35.780
Can I run this other command?

00:08:35.940 --> 00:08:36.240
Yes.

00:08:36.240 --> 00:08:40.720
And so you can say, just stop asking right now.

00:08:40.840 --> 00:08:41.660
I trust you.

00:08:41.900 --> 00:08:43.140
But should you?

00:08:43.220 --> 00:08:43.620
I don't know.

00:08:44.000 --> 00:08:50.400
So if you've got private data on your device, so there's something to be concerned about.

00:08:50.680 --> 00:08:53.560
So one of these solutions is sandboxing.

00:08:54.160 --> 00:08:55.560
And you can...

00:08:55.560 --> 00:09:02.840
Or one of the solutions is create a VM and just don't put the stuff on the VM that you only want the AI to use.

00:09:03.220 --> 00:09:03.860
That's a lot.

00:09:04.000 --> 00:09:04.960
That's a little...

00:09:04.960 --> 00:09:05.860
That's extra.

00:09:05.860 --> 00:09:06.960
That's a little extra.

00:09:07.240 --> 00:09:11.880
And it's for people that are normally using VMs might be fine.

00:09:12.120 --> 00:09:17.100
Or either virtual machines or those other things.

00:09:18.200 --> 00:09:18.900
Containers, right?

00:09:18.960 --> 00:09:20.960
If they're normally using containers, great.

00:09:21.220 --> 00:09:24.340
But if that's not your normal workflow, that's a little...

00:09:24.340 --> 00:09:25.720
